# Architecture Rules

- Follow clean and scalable architecture principles.
- Prioritize maintainability over fast implementation.
- Avoid tightly coupled modules.
- Keep domain logic isolated from framework-specific code.
- Prefer service-oriented design.
- Use dependency injection whenever possible.
- Avoid global state.
- Use composition over inheritance.
- Avoid premature abstractions.
- Keep implementations simple and explicit.

# Backend Structure

- Controllers must remain thin.
- Business rules belong in services/actions.
- Validation belongs in Form Requests.
- Data formatting belongs in API Resources.
- Database access must remain centralized and predictable.

# Frontend Structure

- UI components must remain reusable and isolated.
- Avoid business logic inside components.
- Separate state management from presentation.

# Scalability

- Design features considering horizontal scalability.
- Avoid synchronous heavy operations during requests.
- Use queues for expensive tasks.
- Realtime systems must handle concurrency safely.

# Maintainability

- Never duplicate business logic.
- Prefer explicit naming.
- Refactor repetitive code.
- Keep files small and focused.

# Documentation

- Explain architectural decisions when introducing new patterns.
- Keep README and docs updated when major changes happen.